<BR><br><font style="font-size:10"><A href="http://www.andreasen.org/bartle/test.cgi">Explorer-66% Killer-60% Socializer-46% Achiever-26%</A></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=liquidated>Liquidated</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grumpy Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 3550<br> <font color=#330000>(6/7/04 8:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19472.topic&index=95>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> few things</span><hr size=1> First, thanks prathun and rytan for contributing.. means a lot.<br>
<br>
Second people, wake up, the person the original &quot;% mana&quot; quote came from is none other than Qhue, the gnome Enchanter that's been trolling these boards for years. This guy loves nothing more than to come here and yank chains. I mean I could pester the chanter board all day and tell them charm is overpowered and chanters need to be nerfed all day... But to be honest, where IS the chanter board? I've no idea.<br>
<br>
Qhue may honestly believe what he posted but his vision is warped by his Longstanding hatred for bards. It's been going on  for years now and no idea what's it's done to the guy. Let the gnome rant and rave himself to sleep, he's old news.<br>
<br>
Regardless.... the third..<br>
<br>
The main use I have for fade on raids is to ditch rampage...<br>
<br>
I don't need to Flush (initial aggro on mobs to root them out) ever because my mana is very limited for sustained pulling, and well I have 3 going on 4 REALLY good monks that can flop fd left and right all day. <br>
<br>
For picking.... I only use fade when the tanks don't taunt it off me in time and I really don;t feel like letting the attentive healer take my minimal aggro from me.<br>
<br>
In terms of can a bard (or team of bards) alone pick encounters apart? Yes. Can a pack of monks do the same with fd? yup. Could SK's pull too if anyone on my server was still playing them? Dunno the few we have are the non pulling variety.<br>
<br>
Tell me this though, what's stronger in terms of exploiting grouped mobs?  monks alone, sk's alone, bards alone, or all 3 working as a team? I'll won;t spoil the correct answer for you.<br>
<br>
Why do I even single out those classes? All three have a way to drop aggro and can tank a 2000 hitting mob for enough time to fade/fd (necros just die, but they get res). Both skills trivialize many situations in terms of pulling.<br>
<br>
When skills need to be tweaked for raid level encounters, both skills are interchangeable in terms of overpowered. Nerf one, nerf the other.<br>
<br>
So back to the heart of how I use fade on raids..... Ditching rampage..... that is, get on rampage list and the ability to drop it completely and start over with a fade.<br>
<br>
Back in the pre fade days of ssra, if a bard got on ramp, they died. This meant that any bard playing aoe mana or resists (or the dreaded main tank bard) at the start of the fight was dead meat. So we learned to try and time when to even start our songs. When we guessed wrong, the guild was out a bard for the rest of that fight cause ramp was absolute and ressing us killed us again. We errred on the side of overcaution we not only let our guild down, we incurred the curse of the ancient clerical &quot;where's mana song?&quot; tellS.&lt;-- big S<br>
<br>
I was wracking up 12+ deaths a day easy. Pun intended.<br>
<br>
Enter in pop /w fade and the blam, bards lived lots longer. Bards not only survived, but generally were the last people standing (the necros were fd long before then) on a wipe.<br>
<br>
So the encounters were tuned for this newfound survivability of bards. Enter in such amazingly ugly aoes like terris thule and sayrin's (in Time B) mana drain aoes of amazing range.<br>
<br>
Now to even fight these mobs, aoe resists (and mana song) are expected to be up before the tank is even sent off to aggro the boss. If not for fade, bards would be dying before even the &quot;suicide chanter tashings of tovn era&quot; and stay, as the rats in cod would say, &quot;Dead, Dead.&quot;<br>
<br>
So what's fade really allow a non pulling bard do? Ignore rampage so long as the bard can survive one round of hits and not get low hp aggro. This in turn allows bards to be the always on mana/resist machines the clerics feverishly dream about (go figure terris thule would have something to do with those dreams). <br>
<br>
With fade disabled 100% on certain mobs...... enter in the glorious ssra and VT days of yore...<br>
<br>
Well I'll give you devs who still may be reading, a leg up....<br>
<br>
<br>
Don't give the fd/fade immune mobs insane rampage range and damage.<br>
<br>
Don't give the fd/fade immune mobs insane aoe's that require bards to play resists before the fight starts.<br>
<br>
Combine those two (any one is fine) into a single encounter and you have a situation where the actions the bard is *demanded* to perform ala time, and kills said bard over and over and over and over like the good old days. <br>
<br>
Yup Liq remembers temple of cazic at level 32. The proud birth place of  the one lined sig of &quot;51 Bard, where looking good dead is job number one.&quot;<br>
<br>
Find ways to make fd/fade immune mobs lose rampage targets that fade. Yes they are still on aggro list and a solo bard or monk will still get steamrolled, but get them off the bloody rampage.<br>
<br>
Yup good old Liq, planning DOOM months in advance as always. Thanks for staying for the ride.<br>
<br>
Cheers!<br>
-Liq'd <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=liquidated>Liquidated</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grumpy Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 3551<br> <font color=#330000>(6/7/04 8:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19472.topic&index=96>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> oh yeah!</span><hr size=1> For 'cleric-fication',<br>
